programme.title: Natural World
programme.desc: The world's biggest beasts have always captured the imagination, but whilst being big can have its advantages, it also comes with sizeable challenges. The Komodo dragon's huge appetite means it must take on prey ten times its weight.

programme.title: Walking with Dinosaurs
programme.desc: The life of the first reptilian carnivores on Earth, told through computer animation.

programme.title: Walking with Dinosaurs
programme.desc: The Jurassic period saw the advent of the largest and strongest dinosaurs that ever roamed the Earth.

programme.title: Walking with Dinosaurs
programme.desc: A look at the world as it was 149 million years ago - in the late Jurassic Period. The old continents have broken up and much of the land is under water. Huge shallow seas have supported a revolution in marine life.

programme.title: Walking with Dinosaurs
programme.desc: With wings longer than those of a small plane, pterosaurs were the largest creatures ever known to have flown.

programme.title: Walking with Dinosaurs
programme.desc: This programme looks at the Cretaceous period, 106 million years ago. Volcanic activity forces the continents apart, and dinosaurs diversify into a range of species to cope with environmental extremes.

programme.title: Walking with Dinosaurs
programme.desc: It is the late Cretaceous period and Tyrannosaurus rex is the top predator, but the Earth is poisoned by volcanic activity and a comet strikes.

programme.title: Horizon
programme.desc: Exploring the idea of human coexistence with dinosaurs. Had the species not disappeared from the face of earth ages ago, keeping them as pets could have been a possibility.

programme.title: Planet Dinosaur
programme.desc: It is only in recent years that experts have unearthed the biggest dinosaurs that ever lived. One monster eclipsed all others, more than seven times as heavy as diplodocus was the immense argentinosaurus.

programme.title: Planet Dinosaur
programme.desc: A new generation of carnivores was about to take killing to the next level. At the end of the Cretaceous period, these new hunter killers had spread throughout the globe.

programme.title: Wildest India: Ganges: River of Life
programme.desc: Then watch, the longest river in India, The Ganges. It's a lifeline to wild animals, from rhinoceros and river dolphins to otters and gharials.

programme.title: Wildest India: Thar Desert: Sacred Sands
programme.desc: Covering 200,000 km sq, India's Thar desert is one of the harshest places on Earth. Desiccating winds and near permanent drought has earned this unforgiving land another name: the region of death.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Madagascar: Islands of Monsters
programme.desc: Madagascar is truly a weird and wonderful land. Isolated on an island of extreme and magical looking locations, life has adapted and diversified. With few predators, numbers have proliferated and natural selection has gone mad.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Zambezi: Wild Water
programme.desc: The Zambezi is one of Africa's most influential rivers. It supports some of the continent's most spectacular wildlife. However, the Zambezi's long and winding journey destroys, as well as creates.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Mount Kenya: African Heart of Ice
programme.desc: Mount Kenya soars over 5km into the air. It is the second highest mountain in Africa. At its summit, temperatures fluctuate from over 30 degrees celsius to below freezing.
programme.sub-title: Mount Kenya: African Heart of Ice

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Ngorongoro: Born of Fire
programme.desc: Ngorongoro is thought to have formed about 2.5 million years ago from a large volcano, whose cone collapsed inward after a major eruption. This fertile land is full of wildlife, from cunning hyena and proud lions to vast herds of wildebeest and elephants.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Namibia: Sands of Time
programme.desc: Namibia is an arid, rough land. However, it has been inhabited for thousands of years, by people as well as animals, and shows no sign of losing popularity with either.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Sahara: Life on the Edge
programme.desc: Watch Africa's Cape Coast that goes from the frigid waters of Cape Point to the sub-tropic seas of Kwazulu-Natal./After, see Africa's Dark Heart in the Congo which is seething with innumerable species./Last,learn about the largest desert in the world.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Congo: the Untamed Heart
programme.desc: Known for centuries as Africa's Dark Heart, the Congo is a multi-layered, three-dimensional world, seething with innumerable species. By peeling back the layers, we discover how this vast rainforest works, and expose the hidden lives of its inhabitants.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Cape Coast: Where Worlds Colide
programme.desc: Watch Africa's Cape Coast that goes from the frigid waters of Cape Point to the sub-tropic seas of Kwazulu-Natal.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Ethiopia: Land of Extremes
programme.desc: Landlocked and surrounded by five countries, Ethiopia is one of east Africa's forgotten lands. Seemingly passive deserts in fact seethe with fire, and cloud-piercing peaks shield a secret Eden of canyons and cliff-tops teeming with life.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Virungas: Land of Ice and Fire
programme.desc: It's home to some of the world's most iconic animals  including the African great apes.
programme.sub-title: Virungas: Land of Ice and Fire

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Lake Turkana: Land of the Crocodile
programme.desc: The largest of Africa's Rift valley lakes, Lake Turkana is at the heart of one of the harshest landscapes on the planet. Despite its hostile environment, man and beast have both worked out a way to survive.
programme.sub-title: Lake Turkana: Land of the Crocodile

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Nile: An African Odyssey
programme.desc: The Nile is the longest river in the world. Ancient Egypt, one of the history's most powerful civilizations, depended hugely upon it. Each year, it flooded, replenishing the fields with fertile silt. This automatic irrigation fueled Egypt's economy.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Okavango: Water in the Desert
programme.desc: The Okavango Delta, a huge emerald oasis in the burning heart of the Kalahari desert, is fed by the Okavango River and this perpetual cycle of wet and dry is the lifeblood of this extraordinary natural Eden.

programme.title: Wildest Islands: Vancouver Island: Rivers of Life
programme.desc: Vancouver island is the largest island off the west coast of North America. Glaciers fuel the flow of some of Canada's tallest waterfalls, and an endless network of rivers and creeks provides the ideal habitat for the pacific salmon.

programme.title: Wildest Islands: Caribbean: The Wild Side of Paradise
programme.desc: The Caribbean is a tropical paradise. From just a few meters wide, to hundreds of kilometers across, each of the over 7,000 islands are different, and each has its own unique wildlife.
programme.sub-title: Caribbean: The Wild Side of Paradise

programme.title: Deadly Disasters: Tsunamis
programme.desc: In Japanese, Tsunami translates to “harbour wave.” They are unleashed when a major disturbance occurs underwater, creating a series of enormous, deadly swells.

programme.title: Deadly Disasters: Hurricanes
programme.desc: With a combination of torrential rain, powerful winds, and devastating storm surges, Hurricanes are among Mother Nature’s most calamitous natural disasters.

programme.title: Deadly Disasters: Cyclones
programme.desc: An intense area of low pressure that forms over warm tropical waters, tropical cyclones are responsible for some of the most catastrophic extreme weather events. Their deadly winds and torrential rain wreak destruction on an unprecedented scale.

programme.title: Deadly Disasters: Mosquitoes
programme.desc: In 2014, Microsoft Founder Bill Gates described the mosquito as the “deadliest animal in the world.” It is estimated by the World Health Organisation that they kill roughly 750,000 people per year.

programme.title: Deadly Disasters: Floods
programme.desc: Even when below your knees, you can still be swept off your feet by the torrent of water. And the danger doesn’t stop there: electric shocks, contaminated water and washed away vehicles are perilous.

programme.title: Deadly Disasters: Famine
programme.desc: Every continent on Earth has experienced this terrifying phenomenon at some point in its history. It’s ravaged the world for centuries, as crop infestation, drought, flooding and disease have killed thousands.

programme.title: Deadly Disasters: Wildfires
programme.desc: With flames roaring to heights of 50 meters or more and temperatures exceeding 1,200°C, the wildfire is one of Mother Nature’s most horrific killers. Wildfires show no signs of stopping and their inexorability on this planet is truly terrifying.

programme.title: Destruction Decoded: MANMADE
programme.desc: When it comes to disasters, mother nature has mankind beat. However, as mankind expands, evolves and technology advances, it comes with dangerous challenges. When errors are made or unforeseen circumstances occur, the results can be devastating.

programme.title: Destruction Decoded: TORNADO
programme.desc: A tornado is a violently rotating column of air extending from the base of a thunderstorm down to the ground. Tornadoes are capable of completely destroying well-made structures, uprooting trees, and hurling objects through the air like deadly missiles.

programme.title: Destruction Decoded: MEGAFLOODS
programme.desc: Water covers two thirds of the earth’s surface, and we are utterly dependent on it, but when this vital ingredient of life unleashes its fury on the planet it becomes the ultimate bringer of death.

programme.title: Destruction Decoded: EARTHQUAKES
programme.desc: Earthquakes happen when tectonic plates suddenly slip causing shock waves to shake the surface of the Earth. They occur on fault lines - the most active are the Ring of Fire in the Pacific Ocean and the San Andreas fault on America’s west coast.

programme.title: Destruction Decoded: CONSTRUCTION
programme.desc: Bridges and tunnels have transformed the way we live, making the inaccessible easy to reach, and turning time consuming journeys into convenient commutes, but when things go wrong they can go very wrong indeed.

programme.title: Destruction Decoded: AIR, LAND AND SEA
programme.desc: Planes, trains and ships, our mass transit systems, have had a profound effect on mankind, making the world smaller and more connected.

programme.title: Destruction Decoded: HURRICANES
programme.desc: Hurricanes, Typhoons and Cyclones all the same thing with different names – what they also have in common is their destructive power! Hurricanes are large, swirling storms and winds from a hurricane can damage buildings or trees.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Monuments & Landmarks
programme.desc: Many of the world’s most significant manmade wonders serve not as dwellings, but as powerful signposts. But more than giving us direction, they tell us a story - they characterize powerful forces, or commemorate power lost.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Island Arks
programme.desc: Cut off from continents, remote islands have become floating arks, attracting migrating species and forging new ones. Take a privileged glimpse into the secret lives of the rare and exotic species that inhabit these lost worlds.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Wetland Animals
programme.desc: Wetland Animals dives into the swamps, rivers, and flood plains of the Everglades, Botswana’s Okavango Delta, Kakadu National Park in Australia, and the Amazon to see deadly crocodiles, piranhas, hippopotamus, flamingo, manatee, and platypus.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Water Adventures
programme.desc: We are captivated by oceans, rivers, and lakes - the power, the flow, the reflective stillness. And as we seek to get closer, we immerse ourselves in an expanding range of aquatic experiences.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Volcanic Islands
programme.desc: They've been worshiped and feared over the millennia. But in the wake of drama and destruction, the elements give rise to cultures and nations so beautiful that we've come to know them as the world's greatest volcanic islands.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Port Cities
programme.desc: Some of the most stunning cities are port cities - Sydney, Rio, Cape Town - and are also some of the most culturally diverse and vibrant. The great maritime cities of the world bridge countries and continents and unite the global community.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Nearshore Islands
programme.desc: Some of the world’s greatest islands are so close that they blend in with the mainland. But regardless of their size and origins, they are often the islands we are drawn to the most, each forging their own unique identity.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Remote Cities
programme.desc: Brave the frontiers of the world’s most remote cities. More than distant trading posts and isolated regional hubs, cities like Alice Springs, Jaipur and even Las Vegas serve as gateways to the wild places of the Earth.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Glaciers
programme.desc: Clinging to the world’s highest mountains and forming ice caps on both poles, glaciers leave an impression on the landscape and on all who bear witness to their splendor.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Rivers
programme.desc: Rivers flow freely - beautiful and powerful waterways that underscore the melody of life. As they meander through the landscape, they shape it, wearing down ranges and deepening valleys, eventually flowing out into the sea.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Coasts
programme.desc: Along coasts, one element ends and another begins. No two days are ever the same on a coastline: the only thing that remains a constant is the timeless power of the sea.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Grassland Animals
programme.desc: Grasslands are the great stages of the natural world where large animals play out spectacular lives in clear view of people, including lions, leopards, elephants, rhinoceros, cheetahs, impalas, kangaroos, wallaby, potoroo, bison, and wolves.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Timeless Cities & Towns
programme.desc: These cities and towns are special places where the past coexists with the present, creating cultures totally unique to their people and their part of the world and adhering to ancient traditions and while introducing modern innovations.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Deserts
programme.desc: For all their reputation as inhospitable places, deserts are full of incredible plants and animals that have adapted to the climate. They are bursting with geological wonders that inspire and are home to some of the most life in the world.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Island Nations
programme.desc: Though many are small in stature, they have punched well above their weight on the global stage. Some are rooted in ancient history, while others are only just beginning to realize their full potential.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Bridges
programme.desc: A bridge is a structure that’s designed to transcend, but a great bridge can define the place where it stands. Symbols of human ingenuity, beauty, and grandeur, bridges connect us not only to each other but also to the past.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Coral Islands
programme.desc: The reef systems that gave rise to coral islands support the vast majority of marine species on our planet, but they are under threat. Explore the delicate balance between exploiting and preserving these extraordinary natural wonders.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Flights
programme.desc: Our experience of the world’s greatest marvels is literally and figuratively elevated when we explore them from the air. Whether you travel by air balloon, helicopter, light aircraft, a grand perspective is always guaranteed.

programme.title: Tony Robinson's VE Day: Minute by Minute
programme.desc: Take a unique look at a pivotal day in the history of the modern world, delving into the key events that made VE Day such a momentous 24 hours.

programme.title: Voices of D-Day Landings
programme.desc: In the early hours of June 6th, 1944 Allied forces began the greatest military assault ever attempted. They came to Normandy by both air and sea with one objective.

programme.title: The Ultimate History of the Messerschmitt
programme.desc: In this program we look at the development of the Bf 109 which flew in all theaters of conflict in which the Luftwaffe was involved. More Bf 109s were built than any other fighter of the era.

programme.title: NEW: The Siege of Malta
programme.desc: At last here is the definitive story of heroism and hardship of a people uniquely and collectively awarded the George Cross 'for gallantry', and told by some of the heroic survivors.

programme.title: World War II: Battles Won and Lost
programme.desc: The battles of the first world war were battles of attrition and trenches; the battles of the second world war were vastly different. In this episode we study tank battles, blitzkrieg, commando raids, amphibious landings, and mobile warfare in the desert.

programme.title: World War II: Battles Won and Lost
programme.desc: The second world war was conflict on an unprecedented scale. Its battles set new marks for the sheer size of forces deployed and for the power of their weapons. In this episode we study the first battle at sea, and the largest army to have ever marched.

programme.title: World War II: Battles Won and Lost
programme.desc: A war that reached every continent and touched every sort of terrain demanded every sort of strategy. In this episode we examine battles fought at sea, and in the jungle, in city streets, invasions from the air, and retreats from the land.

programme.title: World War II: Battles Won and Lost
programme.desc: Battles are almost always about territory. Advancing the front line, seizing the port, the city, the oil field. The fate of nations in the war rose and fell on battles that took territory. Singapore, Monte Casino, Stalingrad...all about territory.

programme.title: World War II: Battles Won and Lost
programme.desc: Every war seized new tactics; some inspired, some desperate, all attempting to influence the course of battles. Campaigns waged against non military targets to demoralize. Suicide missions launched when traditional weapons failed. Rules were rewritten.

programme.title: World War II: Battles Won and Lost
programme.desc: A world war is a patchwork of actions. Land. Sea. Air. Massive, or small scale. The stories of these actions, are just as varied. This episode describes battles of amphibious forces, climate, geography, and the problems of supply.

programme.title: World War II: Battles Won and Lost
programme.desc: Through history, armies marched to face each other on favored ground and clashed to decide a campaign, a war, an empire. With the 20th century that changed. The battles of the WWII happened anywhere and everywhere, in every weather and climate.

programme.title: World War II: Battles Won and Lost
programme.desc: Some words transcend their origins as humble place names. They are carved into history as turning points which influenced the course of WWII, the fate of nations, and the make-up of our world. El Alameine, Okinawa, and Pearl Harbor.

programme.title: NEW: Secret War: The Aristocrat and the Balkan Communists
programme.desc: Fitzroy Maclean, an MP and WWII spy, supported Tito's Communist partisans in Yugoslavia against the Germans, forging a lasting friendship and honored at Tito's funeral post-war.
programme.sub-title: The Aristocrat and the Balkan Communists

programme.title: NEW: Secret War: Agent Garbo
programme.desc: Juan Pujol, MI6's WWII agent "Garbo," created a fictitious spy network in Lisbon, deceiving the Germans with crucial disinformation and influencing their strategies. After the war, MI6 protected him, and he lived in Venezuela until his death in 1988.

programme.title: NEW: Secret War: Christine Granville
programme.desc: Christine Granville, aka Krystyna Skarbek, a brave SOE agent, secured the release of captured comrades from the Gestapo before Operation Dragoon, earning the George Medal.

programme.title: NEW: Secret War: The French Triple Agent
programme.desc: Operation Cockade, led by MI6's double agent Henri Dericourt in 1943, aimed to deceive Germans with sabotage. Despite efforts, Germans withdrew divisions unconvinced. Dericourt faced a post-war treason trial and died in a mysterious 1962 plane crash.

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: The Lost Continent (Atlantis)
programme.desc: As the Nazis rose to power, Himmler and the SS were convinced Atlantis could be found, and instigated a series of archeological expeditions seeking uncover and exploit its secrets.

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: Walking with Witches
programme.desc: Convinced the medieval witch trials were a Judeo-Christian attempt to exterminate the Aryans, Himmler established a special team led by Reinhard Heydrich to build a database of medieval German witchcraft practices.

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: The Quest for the Holy Grail
programme.desc: Revealing the work of a secret team of scientists and scholars established by SS leader Heinrich Himmler to scour the globe seeking the origins of the Aryan race and collect ancient artifacts.

programme.title: Building Britain's Canals: Kennet and Avon
programme.desc: Dan Jones examines the Kennet and Avon canal.

programme.title: Building Britain's Canals: Leeds & Liverpool Canal
programme.desc: This canal turned Liverpool into the busiest port on Earth.

programme.title: Giant Constructions: Moving Bridges
programme.desc: Moving Bridges: Exotic milestones on moveable infrastructure. Historically significant: the Kaiser Wilhelm Bridge and the Michigan Avenue bridge. Mechanically unique: the Pont Jacques, the Gateshead Millennium Bridge or the Scale Lane Bridge.

programme.title: Giant Constructions: Railway Bridges
programme.desc: Railway bridges fascinate through different construction methods from masonry, truss-beam bridges to steel-concrete arch bridge. Heavier loads, faster speeds, more frequently: trains speed over bridges and the maintenance teams face ever larger challenges

programme.title: Giant Constructions: Steel Bridges
programme.desc: Steel bridges are extremely durable and multifunctional, fascinating not only due to its gigantic size but also because of the army of workers keeping the bridges in shape: whether on the historical landmark in Sydney or ultramodern mega bridges in China.

programme.title: Giant Constructions: Road Bridges
programme.desc: Road bridges: gigantic constructions of modern road traffic. Europa and Ganter Bridge, Öresund bridge, Sunshine Skyway and Viaduct de Millau.

programme.title: Giant Constructions: Suspension Bridges
programme.desc: Suspension bridges – impressively wide and stretched high over supporting cables or stay cables. The landscape-shaping icons: The superlative Golden Gate, Akashi Kaikyo, Aizaih, El Baluarte and Russky Bridge.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Power Generator
programme.desc: A three hundred and ninety ton giant on a daring journey: A team of German heavy-lift-specialists have to transport a generator from a disused coal plant to its new operation site 120 kilometers away.

programme.title: Mega Transports: ITER Magnet
programme.desc: This giant magnet will revolutionize the world and energy production in the future. The world's largest nuclear fusion reactor is currently under construction in southern France.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Drilling Rig
programme.desc: A brand-new oil rig, worth 500 million dollar, has to go from South Korea to Europe. The problem is that it is too gigantic for a heavy transport vessel. The solution is to tow it.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Siberian Ice Road
programme.desc: A Mega Transport on one of the most dangerous roads in the world. The Siberian Ice Road. It doesn't forgive mistakes. It's treacherous. And unpredictable.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Giant Antenna
programme.desc: South America. The chelonian Atacama Desert is home to the world's largest radio telescope Atacama Large Millimeter Array Observatory, also known as ALMA.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Mining Truck
programme.desc: If a transporter needs to be transported, if 176 wheels aren't enough to carry its weight and if the load weighs twice as much as the transporter... Then it must be the mother of all mega transports!

programme.title: Mega Transports: Wind Park
programme.desc: A wind park needs to get from Europe to Asia. Over two thousand tons of highly sensitive and valuable cargo. On one of the world's largest heavy lift vessels.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Gigantic Autoliner
programme.desc: A transport to the other side of the globe. The Höegh Trapper is the largest automobile transporter in the world. Two hundred meters long, thirty-six meters wide.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Biggest Containership
programme.desc: When the first ship of the brand-new OOCL-fleet gets underway, more cargo is moved at one time than anywhere else in the world and ever before.

programme.title: Mega Transports: AutoClav
programme.desc: A unique mega transport made of steel and titanium with a special purpose: to extract tons of gold. This so-called autoclave is the biggest of its kind. Its weight: over one thousand tons.

programme.title: Mega Transports: Superyachts
programme.desc: Transporting a ship by a ship - this becomes necessary when the super-rich want their super yacht available on the other side of the world, but do not want to sail it there themselves.

programme.title: The Falcon Lake Incident
programme.desc: Aliens visit Earth often; Canada's 1967 Falcon Lake UFO incident stands out. Canada's frequent sightings make it enigmatic.

programme.title: The UFO Battle of Los Angeles
programme.desc: 1942 LA: A mysterious UFO causes blackout & artillery fire. Remains unexplained.

programme.title: Aliens Among Us: The Michael Wolf Theory
programme.desc: Michael K. Wolf shares 30 years of insights on UFOs, aliens, government projects, and crop circles.

programme.title: Aliens and Pyramids
programme.desc: Many pyramidal structures around the world exhibit strange glyphs of futuristic objects and signs of advanced machining with laser perfection. Was there help from an extraterrestrial source?

programme.title: Alien Abduction: The Mystery Unraveled
programme.desc: This docudrama explores the boundaries of human imagination and fascinating biological phenomena to reveal the scientific roots of a modern-day mythology.

programme.title: Alien Contact: UFO Invaders
programme.desc: Hundreds of UFOs have crashed on Earth. Mankind has witnessed these crashes, communicated with the visitors, even left our planet with them once they are able to return to their worlds, but the most shocking revelation is the reason why they come.

programme.title: Confessions Of An Alien Abductee
programme.desc: Chantelle, Marie and Simon are all alien abductees. These ordinary people share their extraordinary stories as they seek help through the curiously named Anomalous Mind Management Abductee Contactee Helpline, or AMMACH.

programme.title: Alien Cyclops: The Extraordinary Case of Sagrada Familia
programme.desc: In 1963 Brazil, three children witness a UFO in their backyard. An alien cyclops descends, and Mr. Alberto investigates the phenomenon.

programme.title: From the Mothman to the Reptilians: A Guide to Alien Species
programme.desc: Witnesses from around the world have had close encounters with extraterrestrial races, shaping our imagination and becoming cultural phenomena.

programme.title: UFO Hunters II: Tales from the Universe
programme.desc: Italian ufologists explore alien evidence in history & folklore. Have we been watched since ancient times?

programme.title: 27 Alien Encounters
programme.desc: Strange and bizarre UFO encounters abound, but recent Alien encounters by highly credible eyewitnesses are so unusual and perplexing that they challenge our understanding of physics and the Universe as we know it.

programme.title: Area 51, Roswell Crash, Alien Abductions
programme.desc: Area 51 is located at the center of UFO research and legends of extra-terrestrial folklore. It is located six hundred miles west of Roswell, New Mexico, where the infamous Roswell UFO crashed in 1947. Also in this episode The Allagash Alien Abductions .

programme.title: Ancient Aliens and the New World Order 2
programme.desc: Recent discoveries reveal that a highly advanced race of extraterrestrial beings came to Earth in our ancient past, but the shocking realization is that they are still here now, among us and may have a sinister agenda beyond our wildest imaginations.

programme.title: Abducted by Aliens: UFO Encounters of the 4th Kind
programme.desc: Are we being taken by beings from outer space or another dimension? A troubling phenomenon has been occurring for centuries.

programme.title: A Dickens of a Holiday!
programme.desc: To make the 100th anniversary of her hometown’s Victorian festival a success, Cassie invites action movie star and former high school classmate Jake to play Scrooge in 'A Christmas Carol'.

programme.title: A Christmas Tree Grows in Colorado
programme.desc: Erin is planning the town’s Christmas celebration and must win over firefighter Kevin in order to obtain the beautiful spruce tree from his property for the celebration.

programme.title: Lights, Camera, Christmas!
programme.desc: When a holiday rom-com movie shooting in her town needs a costume designer, Kerry, a local shop owner, steps into the role. While working on the movie, she rediscovers her passion for costume design.

programme.title: Ghosts of Christmas Past
programme.desc: Ellie is told by a fortune teller that she must resolve her past and make amends with all of those she ghosted before Christmas and discovers love in the process.

programme.title: Finding Father Christmas
programme.desc: Christmas for Miranda is a painful reminder of the family she never had. Her mother died when she was young, never revealing the identity of her father. But, three days before Christmas, she unexpectedly receives a clue.

programme.title: Our Italian Christmas Memories
programme.desc: The Colucci siblings, in an effort to jog the memory of their grandfather who is struggling with dementia, set out to recreate their late grandmother’s legendary pasta sauce.

programme.title: Candy Cane Christmas
programme.desc: As Phoebe is searching for a new tradition to lift her holiday spirits, she realizes that it's not the traditions we cherish, but the people with whom we share them.

programme.title: All Saints Christmas
programme.desc: Lisette is a popular R&B singer who’s getting ready to travel home to New Orleans for Christmas.

programme.title: The Holiday Sitter
programme.desc: When Sam, a workaholic bachelor, babysits his niece and nephew before the holidays, he recruits help from their handsome neighbor Jason and finds himself in an unexpected romance.

programme.title: A Family Christmas Gift
programme.desc: When Amber spends the holidays with her Aunt Dora and helps plan a fundraising Christmas Concert, it brings Amber closer to her aunt and a new love into her life.

programme.desc: Alone on the open sea! Two Canadians, Bob Lush and Mike Birch, took cameras aboard their yachts during the 1980 Observer Singlehanded Transatlantic Race. The result is more than a record of this prestigious international sailing event.

programme.title: Koromousso Big Sister
programme.desc: This film challenges cultural taboos surrounding female sexuality and explores the fight to take back ownership of bodies and to overcome the trauma of female genital mutilation.

programme.title: Everybodys Children
programme.desc: They arrive underage and alone, often traumatized and seeking asylum in a country completely alien to their own. This documentary is a cinematic portrait of a year in the life of two such teenagers, Joyce and Sallieu.

programme.title: How They Saw Us Is It A Womans World
programme.desc: This film, made especially for television in 1956, embodies the conventional myth that women indirectly exercise power through their ability to manipulate men through sex and marriage.

programme.title: Corral
programme.desc: A portrait of a cowboy rounding up wild horses, lassoing one of the high-spirited animals in the corral, and then going for a glorious plunging ride across the visually spectacular Rocky Mountain foothills in Alberta.

programme.title: Toward Intimacy
programme.desc: Toward Intimacy" celebrates the rights of women with disabilities to pursue intimate relationships. This one-hour film features personal stories from four Canadian women, addressing sexuality, self-esteem, stereotypes, and parenting.

programme.title: Lay Down Your Heart
programme.desc: An accomplished artist, a lifelong performer and a person with Down syndrome, Niall McNeil has built a unique family tree of blood and chosen relations made up of his closest friends and collaborators.

programme.title: Worth Every Minute
programme.desc: A tribute to Pat Schulz, a working-class heroine known for her '50s human and workers' rights battles. This documentary offers a historical view of the women's movement, tracing its roots, early issues, current concerns, and emerging directions.

programme.title: I Want To Be An Engineer
programme.desc: This film provides a lively introduction to the professional and personal lives of three female engineers--just a few of the growing number of women who are opting for "non-traditional" jobs.

programme.title: Waterwalker

programme.title: The Man Who Stole Dreams
programme.desc: This enchanting and magical animation film, an ode to our dreams during the night, celebrates the creative imagination, uniqueness, and the human spirit. The plot involves a man who steals the dreams of villagers, the tries to sell them back to the them.

programme.title: Yul 871

programme.title: Return Home

programme.title: Christmas Land
programme.desc: Christmas Land hat seit dem tragischen Tod von Glinda schon bessere Tage gesehen, und Jules muss viele komplizierte Entscheidungen treffen.

programme.title: Die Weihnachtstruppe
programme.desc: Die arbeitslose Kunstlehrerin Allie möchte Witwer Gordon und seine Töchter wieder für Weihnachten begeistern.

programme.title: Der magische Weihnachtsschmuck
programme.desc: Seit sie an Weihnachten sitzen gelassen wurde, hat Marie (Jessica Lowndes) mit dem Fest der Liebe abgeschlossen. Daran kann auch der Festtagsschmuck nichts ändern, den ihre Mutter ihr täglich zukommen lässt.

programme.title: Ein perfektes Weihnachten
programme.desc: Holly Maddux fehlt zu ihrem Glück nur noch der perfekte Mann. Nach einem Sturz vor dem Geschäft schwebt Holly im siebten Himmel, denn ihr Traummann steht plötzlich vor ihr...

programme.title: Weihnachten in den Highlands
programme.desc: Dieses Weihnachten wird Blair Henderson, eine Parfümexpertin aus New York, von ihrer Chefin ins ferne Schottland geschickt, um einen seltenen Duft zu finden.

programme.title: Die 12 Weihnachtsgeschenke
programme.desc: Als Anna, eine arbeitslose Malerin, nicht mehr über die Runden kommt, wird sie als persönliche Weihnachtseinkäuferin für Marc, einen verklemmten Firmenchef, eingestellt.

programme.title: Return To Christmas Creek
programme.desc: Eine junge Chefin kehrt in ihre Heimatstadt zurück, um die Bedeutung von Weihnachten wiederzuentdecken.

programme.title: Ich bin nicht bereit für Weihnachten
programme.desc: Hollys energiegeladenes, karriereorientiertes Leben gerat vollig aus den Fugem, als sie feststellt, dass sie nicht mehr lugen kann, weil der Weihnachtsmann ihrer Nichte Anna einen besonderen Wunsch erfullt hat.

programme.title: Weihnachten auf königliche Art
programme.desc: Kristin Cooper, die hübsche und talentierte Assistentin einer globalen PR-Firma, wird mit der Leitung der jährlichen Weihnachtsmodenschau und -auktion für den Bekleidungsunternehmer Mr. Carson beauftragt.

programme.title: Weihnachten in der Holly Lane
programme.desc: Die Kindheitsfreundinnen Sarah, Riley und Cat kehren als Erwachsene in ihre Heimatstadt zurück und erinnern sich an die glücklichen Weihnachtsfeste, die sie gemeinsam verbrachten. Sie wollen den Weihnachtszauber von früher wieder zum Leben erwecken.

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: zu Gast in Südtirol

programme.sub-title: zu Gast in Tirols Sport & Vital Park am Achensee

programme.sub-title: zu Gast in St. Veit an der Glan (Kärnten)

programme.title: Freddy Quinn LIVE - Lieder, die das Leben schrieb: Teil 2
programme.desc: GoldStar TV feiert die Showlegende Freddy Quinn mit seinem legendären Abschieds-Konzert aus dem Wiener Konzerthaus. Er begeisterte mit all seinen Evergreens wie "Heimatlos", "La Paloma" und "Junge, komm bald wieder".

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: Berggenuss und Seenspaß
programme.desc: Kärnten hat vielleicht die schönsten Badeseen Österreichs. Viele Sonnentage und Wassertemperaturen bis 28 Grad machen Kärnten zu einem Urlaubsidyll. Musik gibt es von Andreas Gabalier, den jungen Zillertalern, Saso Avsenik und seinen Oberkrainern u.v.a.

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: zu Gast in Antholz
programme.desc: Dagmar Obernosterer begibt sich auf kulinarische Reise durch das schöne Antholzertal und macht Erfahrungen beim Biathlon. Sie blickt auf vergangene Sendungen zurück und begrüßt die Schäfer, Simone, die Alpenoberkrainer, Rudy Giovannini, u.v.a.

programme.title: So schön ist der Norden: Mecklenburg Vorpommern
programme.desc: Mecklenburg-Vorpommern ist eine Reise wert. Alles dreht sich um das Bundesland mit den meisten Nationalparks in Deutschland und um seine herrlichen Schlösser und Herrenhäuser. Musikalische Gäste sind u.a Patrick Lindner, WIND und Susan Ebrahimi.

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute: zu Gast im Defereggental, Osttirol
programme.desc: Diesmal präsentiert Dagmar Obernosterer das Defereggental in Osttirol. In einem der schönsten Hochgebirgstälern der Alpen, mit saftigen Almwiesen, glasklaren Bergseen, seltenen Pflanzen und Tieren präsentieren die Stars der volkstümlichen Musik ihre Hits.

programme.title: Natal em Holly Lane
programme.desc: Na intenção de salvar a casa em que sempre passavam o Natal juntas quando crianças, três amigas se reúnem depois de muitos anos separadas, e a ideia é recuperar a magia do espírito natalino.

programme.title: Para Sempre Natal
programme.desc: Um adolescente arrogante acaba preso em uma fenda temporal na manhã de Natal e acorda todos os dias sem presentes. Para solucionar esse mistério, ele precisará entender que a verdadeira alegria não vem amarrada em um laço.

programme.title: Bebê a Bordo no Natal
programme.desc: Na sequência de “Um Ano Depois Daquele Natal”, nem todo mundo parece estar animado para o Natal da Família Chandler.

programme.title: Casamento De Natal
programme.desc: Maggie é uma editora literária cujo hobby é criar oportunidades de relacionamento entre seus amigos. Quando seu ex-namorado aparece como um autor recém-contratado e bem-sucedido, Maggie precisa examinar suas decisões anteriores.

programme.title: O Verdadeiro Sentido do Amor
programme.desc: Na noite de Natal, o xerife Rick parece ter perdido seu espírito natalino. Quando prende um homem acusado de invadir as casas da vizinhança, o xerife não sabe o que fazer quando o invasor declara ser o Papai Noel em pessoa.

programme.title: José e Maria
programme.desc: Em 30a.C., Herodes reinava sob Israel até que o nascimento do Messias ameaçava a sua soberania. Surge então nessa jornada de fé e milagres uma mulher, Maria e um homem, José, escolhidos por de Deus para cuidar daquele que salvaria a humanidade, Jesus.

programme.title: Um Natal em Canaã
programme.desc: Um fazendeiro viúvo do Texas convida seu novo lar para conhecer a família no Natal, apenas para descobrir que as alegrias da temporada mascaram um anseio muito mais profundo.

programme.title: Um Amor Inesperado
programme.desc: É Natal e Sammi está buscando um pouco de sossego. Viciado em trabalho, Seth vem da cidade grande para explorar um terreno que recebeu de herança e que ele pretende vender antes do final do ano. A tranquilidade de Sammi é interrompida pela chegada de Seth

programme.title: O milagre de natal Jonathan Toomey
programme.desc: Quando um menino perde o presépio de madeira que o liga ao pai morto, sua mãe preocupada convence um entalhador solitário e mal-humorado a criar um substituto e permitir que seu filho o veja trabalhar nele.

programme.title: Antes Só Do Que Mal Acompanhado
programme.desc: Neal só que voltar para Chicago e passar o Dia de Ação de Graças com sua família. Mas ele só se dá mal. Tudo culpa de Del Griffith — um vendedor desbocado que leva Neal a uma busca sem sentido.

programme.title: A Christmas Break
programme.desc: Cuando la maestra Addison Tate se entera de que su escuela va a cerrar, decide hacer que esta Navidad sea especial para sus alumnos. Solicita la ayuda de Danny y la química entre ellos se reaviva cuando salvan la escuela justo antes de Nochebuena.

programme.title: La mejor Navidad
programme.desc: Gloria, enfocada en su trabajo en Miami después de su divorcio, envía a sus hijos a pasar la Navidad con su exmarido en Jalisco. Lo que no imaginan es que esta decisión les va a cambiar la vida.

programme.title: Mejor Solo Que Mal Acompañado
programme.desc: Neal quería volar a Chicago para pasar el Día de Acción de Gracias con su familia. Pero solo consigue problemas. Problemas causados por Del Griffith, un vendedor gritón que lleva a Neal en un viaje salvaje.

programme.title: Enchanted Christmas
programme.desc: Cuando se fue de Utah como una joven viuda, Laura Trudeau dejó atrás a su padre, su amor por la danza y una vieja angustia.

programme.title: Merry and Bright
programme.desc: Después de heredar la empresa de su abuela, Kate contrata a Gabe para ayudar a mejorar la empresa. Pero no todo es camino de rosas; Gabe es un cínico navideño y a Kate le resulta difícil aceptar el cambio, pero mientras trabajan juntos, el amor florece.

programme.title: Un Negocio Brillante
programme.desc: Dos canadienses franceses viajan a Nueva York con la idea de hacerse ricos vendiendo árboles de Navidad. La situación entre ellos es bastante tensa.

programme.title: A Christmas Kiss
programme.desc: La diseñadora de interiores de lujo Priscilla Hall y su asistente Wendy compiten por la atención del novio de Priscilla, miembro de la alta sociedad, mientras decoran su casa para las fiestas.

programme.title: Spotlight on Christmas
programme.desc: Abandonada dos semanas antes de Navidad, la actriz de Hollywood Olivia O'Hara regresa en secreto a su pequeña ciudad natal para evitar a la prensa. Cuando se topa con el profesor de secundaria Casey, él la anima a dirigir la obra navideña de su escuela.

programme.title: Enchanted Christmas
programme.desc: Cuando se fue de Utah como una joven viuda, Laura Trudeau dejó atrás a su padre, su amor por la danza y una vieja angustia.

programme.title: Niñero para navidad
programme.desc: Para salvar su negocio y darle una feliz Navidad a su sobrina, la organizadora de eventos Celeste necesita ayuda. Pero cuando la niñera que contrata resulta ser un hombre, se da cuenta de que quizás también haya encontrado el amor navideño para ella.

programme.title: A Christmas Break
programme.desc: Cuando la maestra Addison Tate se entera de que su escuela va a cerrar, decide hacer que esta Navidad sea especial para sus alumnos. Solicita la ayuda de Danny y la química entre ellos se reaviva cuando salvan la escuela justo antes de Nochebuena.

programme.title: La mejor Navidad
programme.desc: Gloria, enfocada en su trabajo en Miami después de su divorcio, envía a sus hijos a pasar la Navidad con su exmarido en Jalisco. Lo que no imaginan es que esta decisión les va a cambiar la vida.

programme.title: Mejor Solo Que Mal Acompañado
programme.desc: Neal quería volar a Chicago para pasar el Día de Acción de Gracias con su familia. Pero solo consigue problemas. Problemas causados por Del Griffith, un vendedor gritón que lleva a Neal en un viaje salvaje.

programme.title: Enchanted Christmas
programme.desc: Cuando se fue de Utah como una joven viuda, Laura Trudeau dejó atrás a su padre, su amor por la danza y una vieja angustia.

programme.title: Merry and Bright
programme.desc: Después de heredar la empresa de su abuela, Kate contrata a Gabe para ayudar a mejorar la empresa. Pero no todo es camino de rosas; Gabe es un cínico navideño y a Kate le resulta difícil aceptar el cambio, pero mientras trabajan juntos, el amor florece.

programme.title: Un Negocio Brillante
programme.desc: Dos canadienses franceses viajan a Nueva York con la idea de hacerse ricos vendiendo árboles de Navidad. La situación entre ellos es bastante tensa.

programme.title: A Christmas Kiss
programme.desc: La diseñadora de interiores de lujo Priscilla Hall y su asistente Wendy compiten por la atención del novio de Priscilla, miembro de la alta sociedad, mientras decoran su casa para las fiestas.

programme.title: Spotlight on Christmas
programme.desc: Abandonada dos semanas antes de Navidad, la actriz de Hollywood Olivia O'Hara regresa en secreto a su pequeña ciudad natal para evitar a la prensa. Cuando se topa con el profesor de secundaria Casey, él la anima a dirigir la obra navideña de su escuela.

programme.title: Enchanted Christmas
programme.desc: Cuando se fue de Utah como una joven viuda, Laura Trudeau dejó atrás a su padre, su amor por la danza y una vieja angustia.

programme.title: Niñero para navidad
programme.desc: Para salvar su negocio y darle una feliz Navidad a su sobrina, la organizadora de eventos Celeste necesita ayuda. Pero cuando la niñera que contrata resulta ser un hombre, se da cuenta de que quizás también haya encontrado el amor navideño para ella.

programme.title: A Christmas Break

programme.title: La mejor Navidad
programme.desc: Gloria, enfocada en su trabajo en Miami después de su divorcio, envía a sus hijos a pasar la Navidad con su exmarido en Jalisco. Lo que no imaginan es que esta decisión les va a cambiar la vida.

programme.title: Mejor Solo Que Mal Acompañado
programme.desc: Neal quería volar a Chicago para pasar el Día de Acción de Gracias con su familia. Pero solo consigue problemas. Problemas causados por Del Griffith, un vendedor gritón que lleva a Neal en un viaje salvaje.

programme.title: Enchanted Christmas
programme.desc: Cuando se fue de Utah como una joven viuda, Laura Trudeau dejó atrás a su padre, su amor por la danza y una vieja angustia.

programme.title: Merry and Bright
programme.desc: Después de heredar la empresa de su abuela, Kate contrata a Gabe para ayudar a mejorar la empresa. Pero no todo es camino de rosas; Gabe es un cínico navideño y a Kate le resulta difícil aceptar el cambio, pero mientras trabajan juntos, el amor florece.

programme.title: Un Negocio Brillante
programme.desc: Dos canadienses franceses viajan a Nueva York con la idea de hacerse ricos vendiendo árboles de Navidad. La situación entre ellos es bastante tensa.

programme.title: A Christmas Kiss
programme.desc: La diseñadora de interiores de lujo Priscilla Hall y su asistente Wendy compiten por la atención del novio de Priscilla, miembro de la alta sociedad, mientras decoran su casa para las fiestas.

programme.title: Spotlight on Christmas
programme.desc: Abandonada dos semanas antes de Navidad, la actriz de Hollywood Olivia O'Hara regresa en secreto a su pequeña ciudad natal para evitar a la prensa. Cuando se topa con el profesor de secundaria Casey, él la anima a dirigir la obra navideña de su escuela.

programme.title: Mitten im Südafrika
programme.desc: Andreas lange Reise führt ihn schließlich und endlich in den Busch – ins „echte“ Afrika. Hier begibt er sich auf die Fährte der typischsten wilden Afrikaner – der Big Five. Und wo könnte er das besser als im Krüger Nationalpark, dem Wahrzeichen Südafrikas.

programme.title: DIE HALBINSEL
programme.desc: Die Küste der Iberischen Halbinsel trifft sowohl auf den Atlantischen Ozean als auch auf das Mittelmeer. Es ist einer der reichsten ozeanischen Lebensräume Europas. Es beherbergt Tausende von Wildtierarten. Entlang der 3000 km² großen Küste finden wir schroffe Klippen, Dünensysteme und ausgedehnte Sandstrände, Flussmündungen und Marschland. Alle diese Landschaften sind ein geologisches Zeugnis der Vergangenheit der Halbinsel und jede von ihnen beherbergt unterschiedliche Lebensformen, die zum Gleichgewicht der natürlichen Welt beitragen.

programme.title: Unsere Wilde Schweiz, Staffel 2
programme.desc: Inmitten von himmlisch schönen Bergeshöhen thront der Piz Beverin über dem Naturpark, dem er seinen Namen verleiht. Zu seinen Füßen erstreckt sich eine Landschaft voller wilder Natur. Tiefe Schluchten und glasklare Bergseen, artenreiche Trockenwiesen und seltene Moore, majestätische Steinböcke und zurückkehrende Wölfe.

programme.title: Naturparadiese in Lateinamerika: Venezuela
programme.desc: Diese Serie feiert Lateinamerikas dramatischste Regionen, von den Hohen Anden zum dampfenden Amazonas, von den windigen Steppen Patagoniens zu den Sümpfen Venezuelas – atemberaubende Schönheit und eine aufregende, vielfältige Tierwelt.

programme.title: Wildes Portugal: Vom Flachland bis in die Berge
programme.desc: Portugal ist ein kleines Land, jedoch bekannt für abwechslungsreiche Landschaften. Korkeichenwälder im Süden am Targus-Fluss und bewaldete Berge am Douro-Fluss im Norden. Entsprechend vielfältig ist die Tierwelt, die wir kennenlernen.

programme.title: Wilde Schönheiten: Türkei
programme.desc: Im Mittleren Osten trifft Ost auf West, Wälder treffen auf Wüsten, die Tierwelt ist erstaunlich. Die weiten Landschaften der Türkei reichen von schneebedeckten Bergen zu Korallenriffen. Auch die anderen Länder sind alle einzigartig.

programme.title: Mitten im Südafrika
programme.desc: Andreas lange Reise führt ihn schließlich und endlich in den Busch – ins „echte“ Afrika. Hier begibt er sich auf die Fährte der typischsten wilden Afrikaner – der Big Five. Und wo könnte er das besser als im Krüger Nationalpark, dem Wahrzeichen Südafrikas.

programme.title: Der Hoplias aimara
programme.desc: Jeremy Wade sucht in Japan nach dem Kappa, einem Fisch, um den sich viele Legenden ranken.

programme.title: Neunaugen
programme.desc: Jeremy Wade reist nach Kolumbien, um eine Kreatur zu finden, die eine frischgebackene Ehefrau getötet haben soll.

programme.title: Der sambische Wunduwels
programme.desc: Jeremy Wade reist in den Himalaya, um den Angriffen an den Flüssen nachzugehen.

programme.title: Die Titanic des Amazonas
programme.desc: Im entlegenen Amazonasgebiet sucht Jeremy Wade nach einem Raubtier, das sich nicht mit der Angel fangen lässt.

programme.title: Der australische Flusshai
programme.desc: Jeremy Wade kehrt zum australischen Fitzroy River zurück und begibt sich auf seine bisher schwierigste Mission.

programme.title: Der Alligatorhecht
programme.desc: Der Extremangler Jeremy Wade sucht in Texas nach dem bösartigen Alligatorhecht.

programme.title: Der Schlangenkopffisch
programme.desc: Jeremy Wade reist den Kongo-Fluss hinauf und sucht nach dem wilden Riesentigerfisch.

programme.title: Der mongolische Taimen
programme.desc: Der Extremangler Jeremy Wade reist zum Sambesi-Fluss in Afrika.

programme.title: Sardiniens wertvolle Muschelseide
programme.desc: Planet Wetlweit: Jedes Frühjahr findet auf Sardinien eine Prozession zu Ehren des Heiligen Antiochus statt. Die Einwohner legen Kostüme an, in den Kirchen werden Altartücher ausgelegt, die noch mit Muschelseide verziert sind - jenen Fasern, die die Fischer seit Jahrhunderten dem Meer entnahmen. Inzwischen sind diese Muscheln streng geschützt

programme.title: Cordóba, die Stadt der Patios
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Der ganze Stolz von Córdoba sind die Patios der Stadt - begrünte Innenhöfe, deren Wurzeln bis in die römische Antike und die Zeit der maurischen Herrschaft in Andalusien zurückreichen. Einmal im Jahr findet ein traditioneller Wettbewerb statt. Dann dreht sich alles um die Frage: Wer hat den schönsten Patio der ganzen Stadt?

programme.title: Kourou: Palmen, Raketen, Gefängnisinseln
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Lange war Französisch-Guayana an der Küste Südamerikas ein Schreckensort für Gefangene. Die Zuchthäuser dort galten als die härtesten Frankreichs. Heute sind von ihnen nur noch Ruinen übrig, die restauriert werden. Frankreich beginnt, dieses dunkle Kapitel seiner Geschichte aufzuarbeiten, nur einige Kilometer entfernt vom Weltraumbahnhof Kourou.

programme.title: Die Minenratten von Tansania
programme.desc: Im Forschungszentrum der Organisation APOPO in Tansania herrscht helle Aufregung: Eine Rattenmutter hat Junge geworfen - ein Riesenerfolg bei in Gefangenschaft lebenden Riesenhamsterratten. Schnell zeigt sich, dass einer der Rattenjungen besonders aufgeweckt ist. Er bekommt den Namen Ronaldinho. In nur wenigen Wochen lernt das intelligente Tier gefährliches TNT zu erschnüffeln.

programme.title: Montenegro
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Noch vor wenigen Jahren waren Esel in Montenegro vom Aussterben bedroht. Dass es die treuen Helfer noch immer gibt, ist vor allem Darko Savelji¿ zu verdanken. 2015 rettete der Biologe die erste, in elenden Verhältnissen gehaltene Eselstute. Kurze Zeit später nahm er zwei andere Esel zu sich, die als Futter für Jagdhunde geschlachtet werden sollten.

programme.title: Zuflucht in den Anden
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Am Tag arbeiten sie hart wie Männer. Am Abend verwandeln sie sich in das, als was sie sich fühlen: in Frauen. In ihren Gemeinden wurden sie verachtet und verstoßen. Auf den Kaffeeplantagen der kolumbianischen Anden, haben sie ein Refugium gefunden. Die Gemeinschaft von Transfrauen muss bis heute um ihre Anerkennung kämpfen

programme.title: Die Schweizergarde
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Seit 1506 schützt die Schweizergarde den Papst und seine Residenz. Verändert haben sich jedoch die Methoden und das Umfeld der Elitetruppe. In der traditionellen Renaissance-Uniform steckt heute ein junger, moderner und gut ausgebildeter Schweizer, der bereit ist, sein Leben für die Sicherheit des Papstes zu geben.

programme.title: Die Sonnenmenschen von Tokelau

programme.title: Dexter Gordon, George Gruntz, Guy Pedersen & Daniel Humair
programme.desc: Dexter Gordon: Live in '63 & '64 features three concerts filmed in Holland, Switzerland, and Belgium that highlight the bebop legend's classic style and silky tone. These shows feature legendary side musicians such as Art Taylor (drums) and Kenny Drew (piano), and jazz classics “Blues Walk”, “A Night In Tunisia”, “Body And Soul”, and others. One of the most influential saxophonists in jazz history, Dexter Gordon is captured in sharp form and style in this 70-minute tour de force.

programme.title: Chucho Valdis
programme.desc: Legendary Cuban pianist Chucho Valdés brought his band ‘Jazz Batá 2' to the Malta Jazz Festival on July 19, 2019. The air was thick with anticipation as Valdés took to the stage, revisiting the small-group concept of his mythical 1972 Cuban album ‘Jazz Batá'. The batá repertoire – the deep classical music of West Africa – permeates Valdés' piano solos throughout the concert. Valdés's band consists of Dreiser Durruthy (Batas and vocals), Yaroldy Abreu (percussions and vocals), Abraham Mansfarroll (percussion), Ramón Vazquez Martirena-Bajo (bass guitar). They delivered a performance that reverberated through the historic island.

programme.title: George Shearing & Neil Swanson
programme.sub-title: George Shearing Duo feat. Neil Swainson
programme.desc: British pianist George Shearing enjoyed an international reputation as an instrumentalist, arranger, and composer. Equally at home on the classical concert stage as in jazz clubs, he was recognized for his inventive, orchestrated jazz. In this live recording from the Munich Philharmonie, Shearing played in a duo format with Canadian double bassist Neil Swainson. The repertoire consisted of a selection of compositions by Shearing himself, among them ‘Lullaby Of Birdland', which is a standard in jazz repertoire.

programme.title: Bootsy Collins
programme.sub-title: Casper the Funky Ghost: Bootsy Collins à Vienne
programme.desc: Bootsy Collins, famed for playing with George Clinton and his very own Rubber Band, is used to playing syncopated, hard and relentlessly rhythmic music. With this unique style Bootsy was a major influence on the development of funk. Now in his 60s, the bassist seems animated by a new energy that reflects his new work on the album ‘Tha Funk Capitol of the World'. With this album, Bootsy Collins pays tribute to the artists with whom he worked during his frantic career: from James Brown and Parliament-Funkadelic to Fatboy Slim. During this concert, recorded at the festival Jazz à Vienne, Bootsy maintains that same energy, giving a spectacular show.

programme.title: Christian Scott
programme.sub-title: Christian Scott aTunde Adjuah, The Walk
programme.desc: In 2019, the vibrant city of Sofia, Bulgaria, hosted the International A to JazZ Festival. Among the featured acts was the trailblazing jazz trumpeter Christian Scott aTunde Adjuah. This genre-defying artist captivated the audience with his eclectic “stretch music” an approach that incorporates hip-hop and reaches back through the American canon into African percussion and its rich melodic content. Trumpeter Christian Scott aTunde Adjuah's quintet, which includes drummer Corey Fonville, percussionist Weedie Braimah, pianist Lawrence Fields, and bass guitarist Max Mucha, delivered a performance that defied boundaries and expectations.

programme.title: Tony Bennett
programme.desc: Relive the magic of one of the most beloved crooners in music history in his prime: Tony Bennett! Recorded live in London's Royal Albert Hall on March 2, 1974, this enchanting performance showcases Bennett's remarkable vocal prowess and charisma to full effect. Bennett is accompanied by his musical director Torrie Zito and an orchestra of British musicians that includes Kenny Clare (drums), Don Lusher (trombone), and Kenny Baker (trumpet). Tune in for Bennett's captivating take on songs “The Good Things in Life”, “My Favorite Things”, “My Love”, “I've Got Five Dollars”, “It Don't Mean a Thing”, and “Maybe This Time” in this magical concert recording.

programme.title: Wycliffe Gordon
programme.sub-title: Wynton Marsalis: In This House, on This Morning
programme.desc: The final concert of the Münchner Klaviersommer 1992 was by Wynton Marsalis and his septet. The 31-years-young star trumpeter performed one of his own jazz suites to the sold-out Philharmonie, under the title of ‘In This House, On This Morning'. The concert covers every jazz style, in composition and improvisation, and in both small and grand forms. Marsalis's Septet was made up of Wess Anderson (alto saxophone), Wycliffe Gordon (trombone), Reginald Veal (bass), Herlin Riley (drums), Todd Williams (tenor saxophone), and Eric Reed (piano).

programme.title: Billy Idol
programme.desc: BILLY IDOL an English rock musician, songwriter and actor. Born in Stanmore, Middlesex, Idol first achieved fame in the punk rock era as a member of the band Generation X. Idol then embarked on a successful solo career, and was a member of the MTV-driven "Second British Invasion" of the United States. A series of music videos for songs such as "Dancing with Myself", "White Wedding", "Rebel Yell" and "Eyes Without a Face" made him one of the first MTV stars. Idol continues to tour with guitarist Steve Stevens. Using interviews, news archive and performance this episode reveals the unique aspect of this iconic artist.

programme.title: Quatuor Ebène
programme.desc: Renowned French string quartet Quatuor Ébène marked the 250th birth anniversary of Ludwig van Beethoven (1770-1827) with a remarkable project: recording all of the great composer's sixteen string quartets. For five years, violinists Pierre Colombet and Gabriel Le Magadure, violist Marie Chilemme, and cellist Raphaël Merlin immersed themselves in Beethoven's 650 pages of sheet music. Their efforts culminated in the performance of the composer's complete repertoire for string quartet, which covers three decades of Beethoven's musical creativity, during six impressive concerts at Philharmonie de Paris in the autumn of 2020. Quatuor Ébène explored every facet of Beethoven's string quartet repertoire: from the youthful Opus 18 string quartets to the Razumovsky, Harp, and Serioso quartets (Opus 59, 74, and 95) from his middle period, and finally, the depth of his late quartets (Opus 127 to 135). This program features Quatuor Ébène performing Beethoven's String Quartet No. 3 in D major, Op. 18 No. 3 String Quartet No. 11 in F minor, Op. 95, “Quartetto Serioso” and String Quartet No. 8 in E minor, Op. 59, No. 2, "Razumovsky". This concert performance was recorded at Philharmonie de Paris on November 23, 2020.

programme.title: Matthias Goerne, Vilde Frang, Nicolas Altstaedt & Stathis Karapanos
programme.sub-title: J. S. Bach - Arias, solos, and duets
programme.desc: Baritone Matthias Goerne teams up with violinist Vilde Frang, cellist Nicolas Altstaedt, flutist Stathis Karapanos, and harpsichordist Michaela Hasselt in this program dedicated to the music of J. S. Bach. They perform baritone arias from Bach's most beautiful cantatas, as well as solo pieces and duets. On the program are Sonata No. 3 in C major for violin solo, BWV 1005 arias ‘Hier, in meines Vaters Stätte', BWV 32 and ‘Die Welt mit allen Königreichen', BWV 59 Suite No. 5 in C minor for cello solo, BWV 1011 ‘Wenn Trost und Hülf ermangeln muß', BWV 117 ‘Ja, ja, ich halte Jesum fest', BWV 157 Invention No. 7 in E minor, BWV 778 Invention in A major, BWV 783 and ‘Welt ade, ich bin dein müde', BWV 158. This performance was recorded at St. Mary's Church in Wittenberg, Germany.

programme.title: Elena Bashkirova, Juliane Banse, Emmanuel Pahud & Claudio Bohorquez
programme.desc: The extraordinarily talented pianist Elena Bashkirova has been president of the Felix Mendelssohn-Bartholdy Foundation in Leipzig since October 2020, succeeding legendary conductor Kurt Masur. In this concert at the Mendelssohn House in Leipzig, Bashkirova is joined by soprano Juliane Banse, flutist Emmanuel Pahud, cellist Claudio Bohórquez, clarinettist Karl-Heinz Steffens, and pianist Ohad Ben-Ari in a chamber music program dedicated to the music of Mendelssohn and his sister Fanny Hensel. The program opens with Mendelssohn's Piano Trio in D minor, Op. 49. This is followed by a selection of songs: Mendelssohn's Schilflied ‘Auf dem Teich, dem regungslosen', Op. 71 No. 4, and Reiselied ‘Der Herbstwind rüttelt die Bäume', Op. 34 No. 6 Hensel's Vorwurf, Op. 10 No. 2 Verlust, Op. 9 No. 10 and Sehnsucht, Op. 9 No. 7 Mendelssohn's ‘Allnächtlich im Traume seh ich dich', Op. 86 No. 4 ‘Die Liebende schreibt', Op. 86 No. 3 and Nachtlied ‘Vergangen ist der lichte Tag', Op. 71 No. 6. The program continues with Mendelssohn's Seven Songs without Words, for piano four-hands (Op. 62 Nos. 1-6, and Op. 67 No. 1), and comes to a close with Mendelssohn's Three pieces for clarinet, violoncello and piano (arr. Ernst Naumann), comprising Prelude, Op. 35 No. 4, Songs without Words, Op. 53 No. 2, and Duet, Op. 38 No. 6. This performance was recorded in November 2020.

programme.title: Herbert Blomstedt & Lucerne Festival Orchestra
programme.sub-title: Beethoven - Symphony No. 3 in E-flat major, Op. 55
programme.desc: Maestro Herbert Blomstedt makes his debut with the Lucerne Festival Orchestra at 2020's Lucerne Festival conducting Ludwig van Beethoven's celebrated Symphony No. 3 in E-flat major, Op. 55, “Eroica”. The sprightly Swedish conductor celebrated his 93rd birthday just one month before this performance. This remarkable performance was recorded at the Lucerne Culture and Congress Center (KKL), Switzerland, in August 2020.

programme.title: Costanza Principe
programme.desc: Italian classical pianist Costanza Principe (1993) started playing the piano at age 6, making her public debut at age 7. Before long she would be performing as a soloist with numerous prestigious orchestras in Italy, the UK, France, and South America. Seen here in 2021 at one of Italy's oldest extant Renaissance theatres, the gorgeous Teatro Olimpico in the northern Italian town of Vicenza, Principe performs Johann Sebastian Bach's ‘Concerto italiano' and ‘Ciaccona', as transcribed for piano by Ferruccio Busoni.

programme.title: DIE HALBINSEL
programme.desc: Die Küste der Iberischen Halbinsel trifft sowohl auf den Atlantischen Ozean als auch auf das Mittelmeer. Es ist einer der reichsten ozeanischen Lebensräume Europas. Es beherbergt Tausende von Wildtierarten. Entlang der 3000 km² großen Küste finden wir schroffe Klippen, Dünensysteme und ausgedehnte Sandstrände, Flussmündungen und Marschland. Alle diese Landschaften sind ein geologisches Zeugnis der Vergangenheit der Halbinsel und jede von ihnen beherbergt unterschiedliche Lebensformen, die zum Gleichgewicht der natürlichen Welt beitragen.

programme.title: Unsere Wilde Schweiz, Staffel 2
programme.desc: Inmitten von himmlisch schönen Bergeshöhen thront der Piz Beverin über dem Naturpark, dem er seinen Namen verleiht. Zu seinen Füßen erstreckt sich eine Landschaft voller wilder Natur. Tiefe Schluchten und glasklare Bergseen, artenreiche Trockenwiesen und seltene Moore, majestätische Steinböcke und zurückkehrende Wölfe.

programme.title: Naturparadiese in Lateinamerika: Venezuela

programme.title: Wildes Portugal: Vom Flachland bis in die Berge
programme.desc: Portugal ist ein kleines Land, jedoch bekannt für abwechslungsreiche Landschaften. Korkeichenwälder im Süden am Targus-Fluss und bewaldete Berge am Douro-Fluss im Norden. Entsprechend vielfältig ist die Tierwelt, die wir kennenlernen.

programme.title: Wilde Schönheiten: Türkei

programme.title: Sardiniens wertvolle Muschelseide
programme.desc: Planet Wetlweit: Jedes Frühjahr findet auf Sardinien eine Prozession zu Ehren des Heiligen Antiochus statt. Die Einwohner legen Kostüme an, in den Kirchen werden Altartücher ausgelegt, die noch mit Muschelseide verziert sind - jenen Fasern, die die Fischer seit Jahrhunderten dem Meer entnahmen. Inzwischen sind diese Muscheln streng geschützt

programme.title: Cordóba, die Stadt der Patios
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Der ganze Stolz von Córdoba sind die Patios der Stadt - begrünte Innenhöfe, deren Wurzeln bis in die römische Antike und die Zeit der maurischen Herrschaft in Andalusien zurückreichen. Einmal im Jahr findet ein traditioneller Wettbewerb statt. Dann dreht sich alles um die Frage: Wer hat den schönsten Patio der ganzen Stadt?

programme.title: Kourou: Palmen, Raketen, Gefängnisinseln
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Lange war Französisch-Guayana an der Küste Südamerikas ein Schreckensort für Gefangene. Die Zuchthäuser dort galten als die härtesten Frankreichs. Heute sind von ihnen nur noch Ruinen übrig, die restauriert werden. Frankreich beginnt, dieses dunkle Kapitel seiner Geschichte aufzuarbeiten, nur einige Kilometer entfernt vom Weltraumbahnhof Kourou.

programme.title: Die Minenratten von Tansania
programme.desc: Im Forschungszentrum der Organisation APOPO in Tansania herrscht helle Aufregung: Eine Rattenmutter hat Junge geworfen - ein Riesenerfolg bei in Gefangenschaft lebenden Riesenhamsterratten. Schnell zeigt sich, dass einer der Rattenjungen besonders aufgeweckt ist. Er bekommt den Namen Ronaldinho. In nur wenigen Wochen lernt das intelligente Tier gefährliches TNT zu erschnüffeln.

programme.title: Montenegro
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Noch vor wenigen Jahren waren Esel in Montenegro vom Aussterben bedroht. Dass es die treuen Helfer noch immer gibt, ist vor allem Darko Savelji¿ zu verdanken. 2015 rettete der Biologe die erste, in elenden Verhältnissen gehaltene Eselstute. Kurze Zeit später nahm er zwei andere Esel zu sich, die als Futter für Jagdhunde geschlachtet werden sollten.

programme.title: Zuflucht in den Anden
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Am Tag arbeiten sie hart wie Männer. Am Abend verwandeln sie sich in das, als was sie sich fühlen: in Frauen. In ihren Gemeinden wurden sie verachtet und verstoßen. Auf den Kaffeeplantagen der kolumbianischen Anden, haben sie ein Refugium gefunden. Die Gemeinschaft von Transfrauen muss bis heute um ihre Anerkennung kämpfen

programme.title: Die Schweizergarde
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Seit 1506 schützt die Schweizergarde den Papst und seine Residenz. Verändert haben sich jedoch die Methoden und das Umfeld der Elitetruppe. In der traditionellen Renaissance-Uniform steckt heute ein junger, moderner und gut ausgebildeter Schweizer, der bereit ist, sein Leben für die Sicherheit des Papstes zu geben.

programme.title: Die Sonnenmenschen von Tokelau
programme.desc: Drei einsame Atolle mitten im Pazifik, die zu Pionieren in Sachen Energieerzeugung wurden: Tokelau ist die erste Nation der Welt, die ihre Stromproduktion zu 100 Prozent auf Solarenergie umgestellt hat.

programme.title: Indien
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Indien, das Land der Spiritualität. Heiler und Gurus, sogenannte Babas, berufen sich auf höhere Mächte. Doch es gibt Widerstand gegen den gefährlichen Aberglauben und die Geschäftemacherei mit der oft verzweifelten Hoffnung auf Gesundheit. Rationalisten touren mit ihrem Science-Van im Dienst der Wissenschaft durch das Land und klären auf.

programme.title: Waschbären, unsere neuen Nachbarn?
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Ursprünglich stammen Waschbären aus Nordamerika. Inzwischen breiten sie sich auch in Europa aus. Da sie 2016 von der EU als invasiv, also als Gefahr für das Ökosystem eingestuft wurden, werden sie massiv bejagt. Die Berliner Tierärztin Dr. Mathilde Laininger engagiert sich für ein friedliches Miteinander zwischen Mensch und Waschbär.

Habían estado "zumbando alrededor del coche como moscas". 48 horas después, culparon al conductor del Mercedes, Henri Paul. Se dice que triplicaba la tasa de alcoholemia permitida. programme.title: Miracles of Nature

Scambieremo poi la fresca regione del Baltico con i Caraibi tropicali. Qui dimostreremo che sarebbe sbagliato collegare la provincia cubana di Guantanamo solo alla famosa base navale americana. Per concludere, torneremo nella regione mediterranea dell'Europa per visitare gli abitanti delle Isole Lipari, che continuano a sopravvivere all'ombra di vulcani sempre in fiamme.

programme.title: 종이에 염원을 담다. 지화장
programme.desc: 오래전부터 궁중은 물론, 사가의 잔치, 불교의식, 굿 등에 이르기까지 지화를 사용해 왔습니다. 지화장은 종이를 오려 장식을 해 의식에 사용하기 위한 장엄을 만드는 장인을 말합니다. 한지를 염색하고 오리고 접어 전통 지화의 전승을 묵묵히 이어가는 장인의 섬세한 손기술을 소개합니다. (석용 스님 / 경기무형문화재 지화장 보유자)자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널

programme.title: 그을음으로 먹을 만들다. 먹장
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널먹은 예로부터 선비의 친구 문방사우(먹, 종이, 붓, 벼루) 중 하나로 우리의 뛰어난 기록문화유산들을 만드는 중요한 소재였습니다. 전통방식으로 만들어 지는 먹은 기름은 태워서 그을음으로 만드는 유연먹과 소나무 그을음으로 만드는 송연먹이 있습니다. '한상묵 장인'이 전통 먹가마를 이용하여 송연먹을 제작하는 과정을 함께 감상해봅시다. (한상묵 / 전통 먹장 숙련기술자)

programme.title: 풍요로운 다과 한상. 궁중병과 가을상
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널성큼 다가온 가을과 딱 맞는 궁중병과 가을차림상, 풍요로운 과실을 가득 담은 꽃송편, 가을하면 빠질 수 없는 밤과 대추를 맛있게 졸인 숙실과(생란, 율란, 조란), 그리고 환절기 감기를 물리쳐줄 달달하고 따뜻한 배숙을 준비했습니다. 우리모두 눈으로 먹으러가요! (박영미 / 국가무형문화재 조선왕조궁중음식 이수자)

programme.title: 소박하지만 구수한 맛. 메밀국수
programme.desc: 척박한 땅에서도 쑥쑥 자라나는 메밀이라는 곡식이 가진 특성은 강한 생존력과 함께 강원도 정선의 토속성을 느낄 수 있는 음식입니다. 전통적인 방법으로 메밀국수를 만들며 일상 속 삶의 애환을 담았던 정선아리랑을 현지인의 목소리로 들어봅니다. (김남기 / 강원도 무형문화재 정선아리랑 예능보유자)자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널

programme.title: 선비의 길. 낙죽장도
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널장도는 몸에 지니는 자그마한 칼로 일상생활이나 호신용 또는 장신구로 사용되었는데, 이 장도를 만드는 기능과 그 기능을 가진 사람을 장도장이라 합니다. 장도 중에 낙죽장도는 7마디 이상의 대나무에 선비들이 좋아하는 시문이나 무늬를 인두로 새긴 칼로서 일반 은장도와 달리 선비의 칼로 알려졌어요. (한상봉 / 국가무형문화재 장도장 보유자)

programme.title: 오감이 가득. 궁중병과 다과상
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널오감이 가득한 다과상을 만들어봐요! 쑥이 들어간 경단 쑥구리단자, 밀가루 반죽을 꼬아서 예쁘게 모양을 낸 한과 매작과와 소나무 꽃가루를 이용해 만든 전통음료인 송화밀수까지. 이번에는 청각 뿐만이 아니라 시각, 후각, 미각, 촉각 까지 담아보았습니다. (박영미 / 국가무형문화재 조선왕조궁중음식 이수자)

programme.title: 겨울 전통 다과상. 궁중병과 겨울상
programme.desc: 온돌방에 앉아 두텁두텁 두텁떡과 달달한 개성약과, 따뜻한 수정과 한잔 하고 가세요. 개성약과는 고려시대부터 만들어 먹었고, 중국까지 그 명성이 알려졌던 고급 과자로 파삭한 맛을 내는 것이 특징인데요. 단지, 열량이 좀 높다는 사실.... 그래도 추운 겨울이고 맛있으면 0칼로리! 아시죠? (박영미 / 국가무형문화재 조선왕조궁중음식 이수자)자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널

programme.title: 혼이 담긴 바늘과 색실. 자수장
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널우리 생활 도구에 멋을 놓았던 전통자수. 이를 복원한 김시인 자수장의 '무아지경'의 작업의 순간을 ASMR로 담았습니다. 한땀 한땀 바늘로 이루는 끈기의 미학이라 할 수 있는 전통자수의 아름다움에 빠져봅시다. (김시인 / 경북무형문화재 자수장 보유자)

programme.title: [신비롭고 아름다운 비경] 청송 주산지 EP.1
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널주산지는 조선 경종(1720년) 10월에 준공하였습니다. 주산지의 맑은 물은 주산현 꼭대기 별바위에서 계곡을 따라 흘러 주산지에 머무르고 주왕산 영봉에서 뻗친 울창한 수림으로 둘러싸여 있으며, 물위에 떠있는 듯한 왕버들과 어우러져 별천지에 온 것 같이 한적하면서도 아늑한 분위기를 자아냅니다. ※ 청송 주산지 일원 (명승 제 105호) / 청송세계지질공원 (2017년 유네스코 세계지질공원)

programme.title: [조선왕릉 가을 숲길] 숲길로 이어진 어머니와 아들, 태릉과 강릉
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널서울의 태릉은 조선 제11대 왕 중종의 제2계비인 문정왕후가, 강릉은 조선 제13대 왕 명종과 명종비 인순왕후가 잠들어있는 곳입니다. 두 능은 연결되어있어 태릉에서 호젓한 숲길을 따라 30분 정도 걸으면 강릉까지 한번에 만날 수 있답니다. ※ 서울 태릉과 강릉 (사적 제201호) / 조선왕릉 (2009년 유네스코 세계문화유산)

programme.title: [궁궐 속 비밀의 화원] 창덕궁 낙선재 후원 EP.1
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널낙선재는 헌종 대에 지어진 건물로, 사대부 주택의 형식을 따랐으나 궁궐 침전의 양식이 가미되었습니다. 때문에 다른 곳에서는 쉽게 찾아볼 수 없는 다양한 문양의 장식이 있어 조선 후기 건축의 축적된 기량을 엿볼 수 있죠. 일반인 비공개 지역인 창덕궁 낙선재 후원을 바라보며 휴식을 취해보세요. ※ 창덕궁 낙선재 (보물 1764호) / 창덕궁 (1997년 유네스코 세계문화유산)

programme.title: Dexter Gordon, George Gruntz, Guy Pedersen & Daniel Humair
programme.desc: Dexter Gordon: Live in '63 & '64 features three concerts filmed in Holland, Switzerland, and Belgium that highlight the bebop legend's classic style and silky tone. These shows feature legendary side musicians such as Art Taylor (drums) and Kenny Drew (piano), and jazz classics “Blues Walk”, “A Night In Tunisia”, “Body And Soul”, and others. One of the most influential saxophonists in jazz history, Dexter Gordon is captured in sharp form and style in this 70-minute tour de force.

programme.title: Chucho Valdis
programme.desc: Legendary Cuban pianist Chucho Valdés brought his band ‘Jazz Batá 2' to the Malta Jazz Festival on July 19, 2019. The air was thick with anticipation as Valdés took to the stage, revisiting the small-group concept of his mythical 1972 Cuban album ‘Jazz Batá'. The batá repertoire – the deep classical music of West Africa – permeates Valdés' piano solos throughout the concert. Valdés's band consists of Dreiser Durruthy (Batas and vocals), Yaroldy Abreu (percussions and vocals), Abraham Mansfarroll (percussion), Ramón Vazquez Martirena-Bajo (bass guitar). They delivered a performance that reverberated through the historic island.

programme.title: George Shearing & Neil Swanson
programme.sub-title: George Shearing Duo feat. Neil Swainson
programme.desc: British pianist George Shearing enjoyed an international reputation as an instrumentalist, arranger, and composer. Equally at home on the classical concert stage as in jazz clubs, he was recognized for his inventive, orchestrated jazz. In this live recording from the Munich Philharmonie, Shearing played in a duo format with Canadian double bassist Neil Swainson. The repertoire consisted of a selection of compositions by Shearing himself, among them ‘Lullaby Of Birdland', which is a standard in jazz repertoire.

programme.title: Bootsy Collins
programme.sub-title: Casper the Funky Ghost: Bootsy Collins à Vienne
programme.desc: Bootsy Collins, famed for playing with George Clinton and his very own Rubber Band, is used to playing syncopated, hard and relentlessly rhythmic music. With this unique style Bootsy was a major influence on the development of funk. Now in his 60s, the bassist seems animated by a new energy that reflects his new work on the album ‘Tha Funk Capitol of the World'. With this album, Bootsy Collins pays tribute to the artists with whom he worked during his frantic career: from James Brown and Parliament-Funkadelic to Fatboy Slim. During this concert, recorded at the festival Jazz à Vienne, Bootsy maintains that same energy, giving a spectacular show.

programme.title: Christian Scott
programme.sub-title: Christian Scott aTunde Adjuah, The Walk
programme.desc: In 2019, the vibrant city of Sofia, Bulgaria, hosted the International A to JazZ Festival. Among the featured acts was the trailblazing jazz trumpeter Christian Scott aTunde Adjuah. This genre-defying artist captivated the audience with his eclectic “stretch music” an approach that incorporates hip-hop and reaches back through the American canon into African percussion and its rich melodic content. Trumpeter Christian Scott aTunde Adjuah's quintet, which includes drummer Corey Fonville, percussionist Weedie Braimah, pianist Lawrence Fields, and bass guitarist Max Mucha, delivered a performance that defied boundaries and expectations.

programme.title: Tony Bennett
programme.desc: Relive the magic of one of the most beloved crooners in music history in his prime: Tony Bennett! Recorded live in London's Royal Albert Hall on March 2, 1974, this enchanting performance showcases Bennett's remarkable vocal prowess and charisma to full effect. Bennett is accompanied by his musical director Torrie Zito and an orchestra of British musicians that includes Kenny Clare (drums), Don Lusher (trombone), and Kenny Baker (trumpet). Tune in for Bennett's captivating take on songs “The Good Things in Life”, “My Favorite Things”, “My Love”, “I've Got Five Dollars”, “It Don't Mean a Thing”, and “Maybe This Time” in this magical concert recording.

programme.title: Wycliffe Gordon
programme.sub-title: Wynton Marsalis: In This House, on This Morning
programme.desc: The final concert of the Münchner Klaviersommer 1992 was by Wynton Marsalis and his septet. The 31-years-young star trumpeter performed one of his own jazz suites to the sold-out Philharmonie, under the title of ‘In This House, On This Morning'. The concert covers every jazz style, in composition and improvisation, and in both small and grand forms. Marsalis's Septet was made up of Wess Anderson (alto saxophone), Wycliffe Gordon (trombone), Reginald Veal (bass), Herlin Riley (drums), Todd Williams (tenor saxophone), and Eric Reed (piano).

After a long break, 2017 marks the release of a second, long-waited, album "Blossom". And, for the public, finally the occasion to discover live these new compositions, mixing rock, folk and electro pop. With reggae vibrations that can rub shoulders with house elements, Milky Chance has one of the most singular sounds. With the presence of musicians on stage, and if we believe the listening of the new record, we can expect more electric concerts, more electronic and even more energetic than in the past!

programme.title: Billy Idol
programme.desc: BILLY IDOL an English rock musician, songwriter and actor. Born in Stanmore, Middlesex, Idol first achieved fame in the punk rock era as a member of the band Generation X. Idol then embarked on a successful solo career, and was a member of the MTV-driven "Second British Invasion" of the United States. A series of music videos for songs such as "Dancing with Myself", "White Wedding", "Rebel Yell" and "Eyes Without a Face" made him one of the first MTV stars. Idol continues to tour with guitarist Steve Stevens. Using interviews, news archive and performance this episode reveals the unique aspect of this iconic artist.
